foreign policy – in Russia. It worked for Putin. And, the question became: Who will be calling the shots after Putin engineered his way back to [[Éminence_grise|behind-the-scene power]], when he took the position of the prime minister?", retrieved 18-Jan-2009</ref><ref>[http://www.eurotopics.net/es/presseschau/medienindex/media_articles/archiv_article/ARTICLE25007-Europe-is-sceptical-facing-the-Russian-presidentials, Europe is skeptical facing the Russian presidentials] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20120731141755/http://www.eurotopics.net/es/presseschau/medienindex/media_articles/archiv_article/ARTICLE25007-Europe-is-sceptical-facing-the-Russian-presidentials |date=2012年7月31日 }}, euro|topics Spanish site, English language summary of Swedish press article in <u>Expressen</u>, quoting the article: "Whatever Putin is contemplating, Putinism will emerge as the victor in the upcoming transfer of power," writes the paper. "Well-staged events like the presidential election cannot belie the fact that it's been a while since Russia was a democracy. Yesterday, Amnesty International published a report that finds a dramatic drop in freedom of expression in Russia. Independent media have been silenced, the murder of journalists remains unexplained and police put down protests by the opposition. Today's Russia is led by gangs with close ties to the FSB security service.... The only pluralistic element in Russian politics is the conflict between these gangs. And the Russian people have no say in this power play.", retrieved 18-Jan-2009</ref><ref name="JShelton">{{cite news|url=http://online.wsj.com/public/article_print/SB122039907604792875.html |title=The Market Will Punish Putinism |publisher=The Wall Street Journal |date=3 September 2009 |accessdate=2009-02-10 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090108214546/http://online.wsj.com/public/article_print/SB122039907604792875.html |archivedate=2009-01-08}} </ref>。在普京擔任[[俄羅斯總統|俄羅斯總統]]和[[俄羅斯總理|總理]]期間，[[西罗维基|西罗维基]]（{{lang-ru|силовики́}}）控制大部分的政治和財政權力<ref name=Krysha>[http://2004.novayagazeta.ru/nomer/2004/63n/n63n-s43.shtml Mission "intrusion" is complete!] {{Wayback|url=http://2004.novayagazeta.ru/nomer/2004/63n/n63n-s43.shtml |date=20060723095634 }} by Olga Kryshtanovskaya, 2004, [[Novaya_Gazeta|Novaya Gazeta]] (in Russian)</ref><ref name="Rahn">[http://www.brusselsjournal.com/node/2501 From Communism to Putinism] {{Wayback|url=http://www.brusselsjournal.com/node/2501 |date=20180717183941 }}, by [[Richard_W._Rahn|Richard W. Rahn]], [[The_Brussels_Journal|The Brussels Journal]], 19 September 2007.</ref><ref>[http://www.rferl.org/featuresarticle/2007/08/a728d464-224e-4ba1-8560-ad580c9c1d71.html Russia: Putin May Go, But Can 'Putinism' Survive?] {{Wayback|url=http://www.rferl.org/featuresarticle/2007/08/a728d464-224e-4ba1-8560-ad580c9c1d71.html |date=20080723231816 }}, By Brian Whitmore, [[RFE/RL|RFE/RL]], August 29, 2007</ref>。

== 社會和經濟 ==
[[鮑里斯·涅姆佐夫|鮑里斯·涅姆佐夫]]作出的報告及一些其他說法指，[[經濟自由主義|經濟自由主義]]、缺乏透明度、[[任人唯親|任人唯親]]、[[腐敗|腐敗]]是普京政治制度的特點之一<ref>[http://www.nemtsov.ru/docs/putin-itogi.pdf ''Независимый экспертеый доклад «Путин. Итоги»''] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nemtsov.ru/docs/putin-itogi.pdf |date=20171116082513 }} Experts' report by [[Boris_Nemtsov|Boris Nemtsov]] and [[Vladimir_Milov|Vladimir Milov]] released in February 2008.</ref><ref>[http://www.finiz.ru/cfin/tmpl-art/id_art-937000 За четыре года мздоимство в России выросло почти в десять раз (''Bribe-taking in Russia has increased by nearly ten times'')] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090123083315/http://www.finiz.ru/cfin/tmpl-art/id_art-937000 |date=2009-01-23 }} ''Финансовые известия'' July 21, 2005.</ref><ref>[http://www.voanews.com/english/archive/2006-07/2006-07-13-voa25.cfm Energy Revenues and Corruption Increase in Russia] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081220114542/http://www.voanews.com/english/archive/2006-07/2006-07-13-voa25.cfm |date=2008-12-20 }} [[Voice_of_America|Voice of America]] 13 July 2006.</ref><ref>[http://gazeta.aif.ru/online/aif/1290/04_01 Чума-2005: коррупция] {{Wayback|url=http://gazeta.aif.ru/online/aif/1290/04_01 |date=20141205055817 }} [[Argumenty_i_Fakty|Argumenty i Fakty]] № 29 (1290) July 2005</ref><ref>[http://www.rferl.org/featuresarticle/2005/07/C6FC8C8F-C942-4D9F-897B-564EE730990E.html Russia: Bribery Thriving Under Putin, According To New Report] {{Wayback|url=http://www.rferl.org/featuresarticle/2005/07/C6FC8C8F-C942-4D9F-897B-564EE730990E.html |date=20081012145909 }} [[Radio_Liberty|Radio Liberty]] July 22, 2005</ref><ref>[http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2007/dec/21/russia.topstories3 Putin, the Kremlin power struggle and the $40bn fortune] {{Wayback|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2007/dec/21/russia.topstories3 |date=20080817032240 }} [[The_Guardian|The Guardian]] Dec 21, 2007</ref>。在1999年至2008年秋季，[[俄羅斯經濟|俄羅斯經濟]]正以穩定的步伐增長<ref name="worldbankreports">{{cite web |url=http://web.worldbank.org/WBSITE/EXTERNAL/COUNTRIES/ECAEXT/RUSSIANFEDERATIONEXTN/0,,contentMDK:20888536~menuPK:2445695~pagePK:1497618~piPK:217854~theSitePK:305600,00.html |title=Russian Economic Reports |publisher=Web.worldbank.org |date= |accessdate=2014-03-24 |archive-date=2007-08-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070813073808/http://web.worldbank.org/WBSITE/EXTERNAL/COUNTRIES/ECAEXT/RUSSIANFEDERATIONEXTN/0,,contentMDK:20888536~menuPK:2445695~pagePK:1497618~piPK:217854~theSitePK:305600,00.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，一些專家將其歸因於1998年的[[盧布|盧布]]貶值、[[葉利欽|葉利欽]]年代的結構性改革、油價上漲和西方銀行廉價信貸<ref>{{ru icon}} {{cite news|last=Polukin |first=Alexey |title=К нефти легко примазаться |publisher=[[Novaya_Gazeta|Novaya Gazeta]] |date=10 January 2008 |url=http://www.novayagazeta.ru/data/2008/01/10.html |accessdate=2008-12-29 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090102003527/http://www.novayagazeta.ru/data/2008/01/10.html |archivedate=2009-01-02}}</ref><ref name="Troublepipe">{{cite news |title=Trouble in the pipeline |publisher=The Economist |date=8 May 2008 |url=http://www.economist.com/business/PrinterFriendly.cfm?story_id=11332313 |accessdate=2008-11-26 |archive-date=2008-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081206070639/http://www.economist.com/business/PrinterFriendly.cfm?story_id=11332313 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=The flight from the rouble |publisher=The Economist |date=20 November 2008 |url=http://www.economist.com/world/europe/displaystory.cfm?story_id=12641926 |accessdate=2008-11-26 |archive-date=2008-12-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081227212710/http://www.economist.com/world/europe/displaystory.cfm?story_id=12641926 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。邁克爾·麥克福爾在2004年6月曾指出俄羅斯“令人印象深刻”的短期經濟增長是同時附隨“對媒體自由的破壞、對民間社會的威脅和影響正義的腐敗”<ref>[http://www.americanprogress.org/issues/2004/06/b99061.html The Putin Paradox] {{Wayback|url=http://www.americanprogress.org/issues/2004/06/b99061.html |date=20120513113229 }} by [[Michael_McFaul|Michael McFaul]] June 24, 2004</ref>。普京在兩次總統任內，簽署一系列自由經濟改革的法律，如降低[[利潤稅|利潤稅]]、實施新的[[土地法|土地法]]和新版俄羅斯民法典<ref>{{cite web |last=McFaul |first=Michael |url=http://www.americanprogress.org/issues/2004/06/b99061.html |title=The Putin Paradox |publisher=Americanprogress.org |date=2004-06-24 |accessdate=2014-03-24 |archive-date=2012-05-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120513113229/http://www.americanprogress.org/issues/2004/06/b99061.html |dead-url=yes }}</ref>；在此期間，俄羅斯貧窮人口減少了一半以上<ref name=kommersantstats>[http://www.kommersant.com/page.asp?id=804651 Putin's Eight Years] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090106030952/http://www.kommersant.com/page.asp?id=804651 |date=2009-01-06 }} [[Kommersant|Kommersant]] Retrieved on 4 May 2008</ref><ref name="stats">[http://en.rian.ru/analysis/20080301/100381963.html Russia’s economy under Vladimir Putin: achievements and failures] {{Wayback|url=http://en.rian.ru/analysis/20080301/100381963.html |date=20130913020517 }} [[RIA_Novosti|RIA Novosti]] Retrieved on 1 May 2008</ref>，實際國內生產總值亦迅速增長<ref name="news.xinhuanet.com">[http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2008-02/09/content_7582876.htm Putin visions new development plans for Russia] {{Wayback|url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2008-02/09/content_7582876.htm |date=20170201035903 }} [[China_Economic_Information_Service|China Economic Information Service]] Retrieved on 8 May 2008</ref>。

內政方面，普京強調國家利益優先於個人利益，主权先于人权，限制公民權利，鎮壓[[公民社会|公民社會]]，將反對派解釋為外国敵對勢力(消除和邊緣化不受當局控制的政黨)，並用行政手段將其趕出政治領域(實際上廢除[[三權分立|三權分立]]制度，建立對司法和立法制度的控制和支配，反对[[司法獨立|司法独立]])，也對該國主要電視頻道的直接或間接國家控制、舆论審查。

== 外交 ==
{{main|弗拉基米爾·普京推行的外交政策}}
在外交事務中，普京政權試圖據稱仿效前蘇聯的偉大、好戰和[[擴張主義|擴張主義]]<ref>[http://www.ej.ru/?a=note&id=5920 Путинизм как лошадь Мюнхгаузена] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ej.ru/?a=note&id=5920 |date=20180829175328 }} ej.ru by [[Dmitry_Oreshkin|Dmitry Oreshkin]], January 24, 2007.</ref><ref name="Teflon">{{cite web|url=http://www.moscowtimes.ru/article/600/42/373358.htm |title=Putin's Teflon Image Takes Hit |publisher=[[The_Moscow_Times|The Moscow Times]] |date=December 23, 2008 |accessdate=2008-12-23 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081225082855/http://www.moscowtimes.ru/article/600/42/373358.htm |archivedate=2008-12-25}}</ref>；在2007年11月，[[衛報|衛報]]西蒙·蒂斯代爾指出，正如俄羅斯曾經向外出口[[馬克思主義|馬克思主義]]，她現在會可能向國際市場推銷普京主義，因為很多時候本能地不民主、[[寡頭政治|寡頭政治]]和腐敗的國家會認為民主、議會和多元化的幌子比真實的一面更具吸引力和更易管理<ref name="Tisd">{{cite news|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2007/nov/21/tisdallbriefing.simontisdall|title=Putinism could be the next Russian export|publisher=The Guardian|date=21 November 2008|accessdate=2009-02-11|location=London|first=Simon|last=Tisdall|archive-date=2012-05-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120506132507/http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2007/nov/21/tisdallbriefing.simontisdall|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 評價 ==
美國經濟學家{{link-en|理查德·W·拉恩|Richard W. Rahn}}在2007年9月指普京主義為“俄羅斯政府的民族主義獨裁，偽裝成一個民主的自由市場”，這“比[[共產主義|共產主義]]更接近[[法西斯主義|法西斯主義]]”<ref name="Rahn"/>，而普京主義令俄羅斯的經濟迅速增長，使大多數人因生活水平提高而願意忍受的“軟鎮壓”<ref name="RRahn"/>，他更預測隨著俄羅斯經濟的命運改變，普京主義會更鎮壓民眾<ref name="RRahn"/>。一名俄羅斯歷史學家曾指，如果民主是由多數人統治，保護少數人的權利和機會，目前的政治體制至少在形式上可以說是民主的。俄羅斯存在多黨政治體系中，反對派在[[國家杜馬|國家杜馬]]有席位<ref name="RRahn">{{cite web|author=[[Richard_W._Rahn|Richard W. Rahn]]|url=http://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2007/sep/20/putinism/|title=Putinism|publisher=[[The_Washington_Times|The Washington Times]]|date=20 September 2008|accessdate=2009-02-11|archive-date=2019-06-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626131013/https://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2007/sep/20/putinism/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

